==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[rhetorica|rhētorica]]''' < {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ῥητορική]]}}''' (rētorikē), feminine form of '''{{polytonic|[[ῥητορικός]]}}''' (rētorikos) "concerning public speech" < '''{{polytonic|[[ῥήτωρ]]}}''' (rētōr) "public speaker"

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# The [[art]] of using [[language]], especially public speaking, as a means to [[persuade]].
# [[meaningless|Meaningless]] [[language]] with an exaggerated style [[intend]]ed to [[impress]].
#:''It's only so much '''rhetoric'''.''

